# --- Canonical evidence policy -------------------------------------------------
# TRACKED (claim-defining, small, recoverable via git):
#   config/*.json   -> frozen model inputs incl. prior-calibration.json (validation-derived tau)
#   doc/*.md, doc/*.json -> verification gate, frozen result summaries, split-equivalence,
#                           cross-dataset + re-freeze reports, evidence-schema2.json
# IGNORED (heavy / regenerable, reproducible from checkpoints + canonical config):
#   outputs/ (per-cell records, checkpoints), dataset/cache (features, morgan cache), *.pt
# Rationale: anything that DEFINES a claim or the frozen operating point lives in config/ or doc/
# (tracked); anything regenerable from those + checkpoints stays ignored. Do not commit *.pt.
